{{Infobox book |italic title=force | name = The Indigenous Remains of Pichilemu | title_orig = Los Restos Indígenas de Pichilemu | translator = | image = Los Restos Indígenas de Pichilemu (1908).JPG | caption = | author = [[José Toribio Medina]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = Chile | language = Spanish | subject = [[History of Pichilemu]], [[History of Chile]], [[Archaeology]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://catalogo.bcn.cl/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=1282P9570E7A2.186923&profile=bcn&uri=link=3100007~!458014~!3100001~!3100002&aspect=subtab146&menu=search&ri=1&source=~!horizon&term=Los+restos+ind%C3%ADgenas+de+Pichilemu+%2F&index=ALTITLP|title=Catálogo Bibliográfico|publisher=}}</ref> | genre = | publisher = Imprenta Cervantes | pub_date = 1908 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = 13 | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Los Restos Indígenas de Pichilemu''''' (''The Indigenous Remains of Pichilemu'') was a 1908 book published by [[Chilean people|Chilean]] [[historiographer]] [[José Toribio Medina]].
Medina presents a report of his examination to indigenous rests found in a [[Pichilemu]] grotto (currently named ''Virgin's Grotto''—{{lang-es|Gruta de la Virgen}}) by [[Agustín Ross]] and Evaristo Merino in 1908. The book contains two sheets, that show some tools that [[Promoucae]]s indigenous used.
